---
import Icon from './Icon.astro';
---

<section id="features" class="scroll-mt-20 mx-auto max-w-7xl px-5 py-20 lg:px-8 lg:py-28">
  <div class="reveal mx-auto max-w-2xl text-center">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-accent">Everything in one reader</p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-[clamp(1.9rem,4vw,2.9rem)] font-semibold leading-tight tracking-tight text-ink dark:text-white">
      The polish you&rsquo;d expect from an app you pay for
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-soft dark:text-slate-300">
      Most read-aloud tools sound robotic and lose your place. ReadAloud was built
      the other way around — accuracy and feel first.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="reveal mt-14 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
    <!-- Hero feature: word-perfect highlighting (spans 2 cols) -->
    <article
      class="group relative overflow-hidden rounded-3xl border border-accent/20 bg-gradient-to-br from-accent-soft/80 to-paper p-7 sm:col-span-2 dark:border-accent-bright/25 dark:from-accent-bright/10 dark:to-night-soft"
    >
      <span class="grid h-11 w-11 place-items-center rounded-2xl bg-accent text-white shadow-md shadow-accent/30">
        <Icon name="highlighter" size={20} />
      </span>
      <h3 class="mt-5 text-xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-white">Word-perfect highlighting, on the live page</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 max-w-lg text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink-soft dark:text-slate-300">
        Every word lights up exactly as it&rsquo;s spoken — painted right over the
        real page with zero changes to it. Your eyes and ears stay in lock-step,
        so nothing gets lost.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-5 font-display text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink dark:text-white">
        Reading becomes <span class="mark">effortless</span> when the words
        <span class="rounded-[0.35em] bg-accent px-1 text-white">keep your place</span> for you.
      </p>
    </article>

    <!-- Two engines -->
    <article class="rounded-3xl border border-paper-dim bg-paper p-7 transition-all hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-xl hover:shadow-slate-900/5 dark:border-night-line dark:bg-night-soft">
      <span class="grid h-11 w-11 place-items-center rounded-2xl bg-paper-warm text-accent dark:bg-night dark:text-accent-soft">
        <Icon name="micVocal" size={20} />
      </span>
      <h3 class="mt-5 text-lg font-semibold text-ink dark:text-white">Voices that sound human</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink-soft dark:text-slate-300">
        Free voices that work offline, or ultra-realistic premium voices you have
        to hear to believe. Pick a favourite and switch anytime.
      </p>
    </article>

    <!-- Languages -->
    <article class="rounded-3xl border border-paper-dim bg-paper p-7 transition-all hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-xl hover:shadow-slate-900/5 dark:border-night-line dark:bg-night-soft">
      <span class="grid h-11 w-11 place-items-center rounded-2xl bg-paper-warm text-accent dark:bg-night dark:text-accent-soft">
        <Icon name="languages" size={20} />
      </span>
      <h3 class="mt-5 text-lg font-semibold text-ink dark:text-white">Reads 30+ languages</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink-soft dark:text-slate-300">
        It detects the language automatically, picks a matching voice, and renders
        right-to-left scripts correctly — no settings to fiddle with.
      </p>
    </article>

    <!-- Files -->
    <article class="rounded-3xl border border-paper-dim bg-paper p-7 transition-all hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-xl hover:shadow-slate-900/5 dark:border-night-line dark:bg-night-soft">
      <span class="grid h-11 w-11 place-items-center rounded-2xl bg-paper-warm text-accent dark:bg-night dark:text-accent-soft">
        <Icon name="fileText" size={20} />
      </span>
      <h3 class="mt-5 text-lg font-semibold text-ink dark:text-white">Not just web pages</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink-soft dark:text-slate-300">
        Drag in a PDF, EPUB, DOCX, or TXT and it opens in a clean reader — even
        long documents start playing the moment you hit play.
      </p>
    </article>

    <!-- TL;DR (spans 2) -->
    <article class="group relative overflow-hidden rounded-3xl border border-paper-dim bg-paper p-7 transition-all hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-xl hover:shadow-slate-900/5 sm:col-span-2 dark:border-night-line dark:bg-night-soft">
      <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
        <div class="max-w-lg">
          <span class="grid h-11 w-11 place-items-center rounded-2xl bg-paper-warm text-accent dark:bg-night dark:text-accent-soft">
            <Icon name="sparkles" size={20} />
          </span>
          <h3 class="mt-5 text-lg font-semibold text-ink dark:text-white">AI TL;DR before you commit</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink-soft dark:text-slate-300">
            Not sure a 4,000-word piece is worth it? Get an instant summary —
            and have <em>that</em> read aloud too, with the same highlighting.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="hidden shrink-0 rounded-2xl border border-paper-dim bg-paper-warm p-4 sm:block dark:border-night-line dark:bg-night">
          <div class="mb-2 flex items-center gap-1.5 text-accent">
            <Icon name="sparkles" size={14} /><span class="text-xs font-semibold">TL;DR</span>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-1.5">
            <span class="block h-1.5 w-32 rounded-full bg-accent/30"></span>
            <span class="block h-1.5 w-28 rounded-full bg-accent/20"></span>
            <span class="block h-1.5 w-20 rounded-full bg-accent/20"></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Privacy -->
    <article class="rounded-3xl border border-paper-dim bg-paper p-7 transition-all hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-xl hover:shadow-slate-900/5 dark:border-night-line dark:bg-night-soft">
      <span class="grid h-11 w-11 place-items-center rounded-2xl bg-paper-warm text-accent dark:bg-night dark:text-accent-soft">
        <Icon name="shield" size={20} />
      </span>
      <h3 class="mt-5 text-lg font-semibold text-ink dark:text-white">Private by design</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink-soft dark:text-slate-300">
        No account. Free voices run entirely on your device. We never touch the
        page&rsquo;s content beyond reading it to you — and never sell a thing.
      </p>
    </article>

    <!-- Controls -->
    <article class="rounded-3xl border border-paper-dim bg-paper p-7 transition-all hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-xl hover:shadow-slate-900/5 dark:border-night-line dark:bg-night-soft">
      <span class="grid h-11 w-11 place-items-center rounded-2xl bg-paper-warm text-accent dark:bg-night dark:text-accent-soft">
        <Icon name="gauge" size={20} />
      </span>
      <h3 class="mt-5 text-lg font-semibold text-ink dark:text-white">Controls that get out of the way</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink-soft dark:text-slate-300">
        Speed 0.5×–3×, skip by sentence, click any word to jump there, Space to
        play, auto-scroll, and a draggable bar that docks where you want it.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
